---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// V9 — FOUNDER LETTER: Notion "Hi there!" / Browser Company style.
// Narrow column, first-person narrative, intimate and conversational.
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Catalyst Neuromorphic" description="Building neuromorphic processors to challenge the way intelligence is computed." hasFog={true}>

  <!-- LETTER -->
  <article class="v9-letter" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">

    <p class="v9-greeting reveal">Hi.</p>

    <p class="reveal">I started Catalyst because I was frustrated.</p>

    <p class="reveal">I kept reading about neuromorphic processors &mdash; chips that compute the way neurons do, event-driven, incredibly efficient &mdash; and every time I tried to actually get access to one, I hit a wall. Intel has Loihi. IBM built TrueNorth. Both are closed, corporate, and inaccessible. If you're not inside those companies or their select research programmes, you don't get access. <strong>The hardware that could reshape computing is locked behind walls.</strong></p>

    <p class="reveal">So I decided to build my own.</p>

    <div class="v9-divider reveal"></div>

    <p class="reveal">Here's the problem I'm trying to solve. <strong>Modern AI runs on hardware that was never designed for intelligence.</strong> GPUs burn hundreds of watts per chip. Data centres already consume over 2% of global electricity, and that share is climbing fast. Training a single large language model can use more energy than a hundred homes do in a year. The models are getting bigger, but the returns are shrinking.</p>

    <p class="reveal">And for all that power, these systems still can't learn from new information without being retrained from scratch. They can't run without a data centre. They can't operate without sending your data to someone else's infrastructure.</p>

    <p class="reveal"><strong>The human brain does all of this on 20 watts.</strong> It learns continuously. It processes information in real-time. It runs at the edge, on-device, with no internet connection required. The gap between biological intelligence and artificial intelligence isn't a software problem. It's a hardware problem.</p>

    <div class="v9-divider reveal"></div>

    <p class="reveal">Neuromorphic chips compute the way neurons do. They're event-driven &mdash; they only consume energy when there's something to process. They can learn on the hardware itself, not just run pre-trained models. They operate at the edge, on-device, without cloud dependency. And they do it at a fraction of the power cost.</p>

    <p class="reveal">This technology exists. But it's locked away. I'm building the open alternative &mdash; full processor designs, published research, and a cloud platform anyone can use today.</p>

    <blockquote class="v9-pullquote reveal">
      We're not asking for permission to compete with billion-dollar companies. We're just doing it.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="v9-divider reveal"></div>

    <p class="reveal">I've designed two processor generations from scratch. Both are built in software, validated on real FPGA hardware, and documented in published papers you can read today. I built a cloud API &mdash; you can run a neuromorphic network right now, from your terminal, without buying anything.</p>

    <p class="reveal">I'm raising funding and building toward manufactured silicon. That's the goal: <strong>a physical chip you can hold, running real neuromorphic intelligence.</strong> I'm not there yet. But the architecture is complete, tested, and protected by patent.</p>

    <div class="v9-divider reveal"></div>

    <p class="reveal">If you want to verify any of this, you can. Read the papers &mdash; they're on Zenodo with DOIs, fully open access. Try the cloud &mdash; the API is live and there's a free tier. Check the hardware &mdash; the designs run on real FPGA boards. Join the community &mdash; the GitHub is open and the backers are growing.</p>

    <p class="reveal">I'm not asking you to take my word for it. I'm asking you to look.</p>

    <p class="v9-signoff reveal">&mdash; Henry</p>

    <p class="v9-founder-bio reveal">Henry Shulayev Barnes &mdash; engineering student at the University of Aberdeen. Started Catalyst because the neuromorphic hardware that should exist doesn't, and the hardware that does exist isn't accessible. Currently a member of Techscaler, Scotland's tech startup community.</p>

  </article>

  <!-- IP -->
  <section class="v9-ip-section" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div class="v9-ip-inner reveal">
      <span class="v9-ip-item">UK Patents Filed Feb 2026</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-sep">&middot;</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-item">RTL BSL 1.1 proprietary</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-sep">&middot;</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-item">SDK BSL 1.1</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-sep">&middot;</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-item">Papers open access Zenodo</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-sep">&middot;</span>
      <span class="v9-ip-item">API Client MIT</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GET IN TOUCH -->
  <section class="connect-section" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif; font-size:clamp(2.4rem,5vw,3.6rem); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.035em; line-height:1.08; text-align:center; margin-bottom:18px;">Get in touch.</h2>
    <p class="connect-email"><a href="mailto:henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com">henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com</a></p>
    <div class="connect-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/catalyst-neuromorphic" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="connect-card"><svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.4 5.4 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65S8.93 17.38 9 18v4"/><path d="M9 18c-4.51 2-5-2-7-2"/></svg><span class="connect-label">GitHub</span><span class="connect-sub">Source &amp; contributions</span></a>
      <a href="/research" class="connect-card"><svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg><span class="connect-label">Research</span><span class="connect-sub">Papers &amp; benchmarks</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style is:global>
    /* ── V9 Letter Container ── */
    .v9-letter {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: clamp(8rem, 12vw, 10rem) 24px 60px;
    }

    /* ── V9 Greeting ── */
    .v9-greeting {
      font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }

    /* ── V9 Body Typography ── */
    .v9-letter > p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .v9-letter > p strong {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* ── V9 Divider ── */
    .v9-divider {
      width: 40px;
      height: 1px;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      margin: 48px 0;
    }

    /* ── V9 Pull Quote ── */
    .v9-pullquote {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
      font-weight: 500;
      border-left: 3px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4);
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin: 48px 0;
      font-style: normal;
    }

    /* ── V9 Sign-off ── */
    .v9-signoff {
      font-style: italic;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6) !important;
      margin-top: 48px !important;
      margin-bottom: 32px !important;
      font-size: 1.1rem !important;
    }

    /* ── V9 Founder Bio ── */
    .v9-founder-bio {
      font-size: 0.88rem !important;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3) !important;
      line-height: 1.7 !important;
      padding-top: 24px;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    }

    /* ── V9 IP Section ── */
    .v9-ip-section {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 24px 60px;
    }
    .v9-ip-inner {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 8px 16px;
      padding: 20px 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    }
    .v9-ip-item {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
    .v9-ip-sep {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    }

    /* ── V9 Responsive ── */
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .v9-letter {
        padding-left: 20px;
        padding-right: 20px;
      }
      .v9-pullquote {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
      }
    }

    /* ── Connect Section ── */
    .connect-section{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px 32px 100px}.connect-email{font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(1.4rem,3vw,2.2rem);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-0.02em;text-align:center;margin-top:16px;margin-bottom:56px}.connect-email a{color:rgba(59,130,246,0.8);text-decoration:none;transition:color 0.3s}.connect-email a:hover{color:#60A5FA}.connect-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:20px}.connect-card{display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;text-align:center;padding:36px 24px;border-radius:20px;text-decoration:none;color:#fff;background:linear-gradient(165deg,rgba(255,255,255,0.12) 0%,rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 35%,rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 100%);backdrop-filter:blur(28px) saturate(190%) brightness(1.06);-webkit-backdrop-filter:blur(28px) saturate(190%) brightness(1.06);border:1px solid transparent;box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.45),inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.14),inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.02);position:relative;overflow:hidden;transition:box-shadow 0.5s,transform 0.3s}.connect-card:hover{transform:translateY(-3px);box-shadow:0 12px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.55),inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.18),inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.03)}.connect-card::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;border-radius:20px;padding:1px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.22) 0%,rgba(59,130,246,0.06) 25%,rgba(59,130,246,0.02) 50%,rgba(59,130,246,0.06) 75%,rgba(59,130,246,0.18) 100%);-webkit-mask:linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box,linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);-webkit-mask-composite:xor;mask-composite:exclude;pointer-events:none;z-index:5;opacity:0.55;transition:opacity 0.4s}.connect-card:hover::before{opacity:1}.connect-card svg{color:#60A5FA;margin-bottom:16px;position:relative;z-index:2}.connect-label{font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px;position:relative;z-index:2}.connect-sub{font-size:0.78rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);position:relative;z-index:2}@media(max-width:640px){.connect-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  </style>

</BaseLayout>
